{
  "text": ". More generally, as long as there is an isometry that allows us to perform a T-duality, we can define both fibrations. Therefore, T-duality can always be interpretated as this sort of interchange. (See Refs. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] for recent discussions.)",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "6041460",
